fields.definition: Experience people have related to approaching the goal. Their mind-state in approaching goal.
Around achieving this goal. Not knowing or concerned about future outcome.
External barrier to achieving their goal.
In achieving goal or on route to achieving goal.
In eventual outcome, but not a current success.
Advice for achieving this goal (student’s advice or someone else’s)
Gaining tools or ambition for how to continue learning throughout their lives.
Cultivating a broadening curiosity.
Getting help in becoming a better critical learner, an ability to be open to new information and experiences and to gain something from them.
Choosing a college.
Experience transitioning to college life as an entering Freshman or as a transfer student from another school.
Choosing a major.
Experience getting into their major of choice.
Strategy to navigate through the UW and into a career.
Experience carrying out their plan to get through the UW and into their career of choice.
Get good grades, graduate, get a job.  Establish myself as successful to myself or others.

Getting help in choosing the UW, choosing their major, and planning /carrying out their trajectory through the UW and into their chosen career.  This includes getting good grades, graduating, making themselves an attractive job candidate, and getting a job.
Working toward self-reliance and self-sufficiency (e.g. laundry, taxes).
Individual development of understanding who they are.
Understanding who they are through relationships with other people.
Finding meaning in future endeavors, setting oneself up for a “meaningful life”
Understanding my place in the world / study abroad /  Diversity
Balancing school/work/life
Get help in understanding who they are and their place in the world. Becoming an autonomous individual.

Far far away, behind the word mountains, far from the countries Vokalia and Consonantia, there live the blind texts. Separated they live in Bookmarksgrove right at the coast of the Semantics, a large language ocean. A small river named Duden flows by their place and supplies it with the necessary regelialia.

It is a paradisematic country, in which roasted parts of sentences fly into your mouth. Even the all-powerful Pointing has no control about the blind texts it is an almost unorthographic life One day however a small line of blind text by the name of Lorem Ipsum decided to leave for the far World of Grammar.

The Big Oxmox advised her not to do so, because there were thousands of bad Commas, wild Question Marks and devious Semikoli, but the Little Blind Text didn’t listen. She packed her seven versalia, put her initial into the belt and made herself on the way.

When she reached the first hills of the Italic Mountains, she had a last view back on the skyline of her hometown Bookmarksgrove, the headline of Alphabet Village and the subline of her own road, the Line Lane. Pityful a rethoric question ran over her cheek, then she continued her way.

On her way she met a copy. The copy warned the Little Blind Text, that where it came from it would have been rewritten a thousand times and everything that was left from its origin would be the word and and the Little Blind Text should turn around and return to its own, safe country.

But nothing the copy said could convince her and so it didn’t take long until a few insidious Copy Writers ambushed her, made her drunk with Longe and Parole and dragged her into their agency, where they abused her for their projects again and again. And if she hasn’t been rewritten, then they are still using her.
